Jiangxi hit by severe drought 
2011-05-19 13:09:30 GMT
Due to unusual lack of waterfalls, Jiangxi was hit by a severe drought that began plaguing in the spring and continued into the summer, which was rare in recent years in the province. The drought left more than 230,000 people in short of drinking water and affected vast areas of rice fields. 

